@page "/features"
@layout MacroSutra.Web.Components.Layout.LandingLayout

<PageTitle>MacroSutra - Features</PageTitle>

<section class="landing-section">
    <div class="landing-container">
        <h1 class="text-center">Features</h1>
        <p class="text-center landing-hero-subtitle">Build, automate, and monitor trading strategies with a complete suite of tools.</p>

        <!-- Strategy Builder -->
        <div class="landing-feature-detail" id="strategies">
            <div class="landing-feature-detail-icon"><i class="fa-duotone fa-chess-knight fa-3x"></i></div>
            <div>
                <h2>Strategy Builder</h2>
                <p>Create sophisticated trading strategies without writing code. Define triggers based on price movements, technical indicators, or market events. Set conditions like position limits, time-of-day windows, and portfolio allocation rules. Attach actions to buy, sell, adjust positions, or send notifications when your criteria are met.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Portfolio Management -->
        <div class="landing-feature-detail" id="portfolio">
            <div class="landing-feature-detail-icon"><i class="fa-duotone fa-chart-pie fa-3x"></i></div>
            <div>
                <h2>Portfolio Management</h2>
                <p>See all your positions, trades, and performance metrics in one place. MacroSutra aggregates data from every connected brokerage into a unified portfolio view. Track realized and unrealized P&amp;L, view position history, and analyze performance over time. Export data or query it via the SDK.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Brokerage Integration -->
        <div class="landing-feature-detail" id="brokerages">
            <div class="landing-feature-detail-icon"><i class="fa-duotone fa-building-columns fa-3x"></i></div>
            <div>
                <h2>Brokerage Integration</h2>
                <p>Connect your brokerage accounts securely using OAuth or API keys. MacroSutra supports 10 brokerages — Alpaca, Charles Schwab, Interactive Brokers, Tradier, Webull, TradeStation, Tastytrade, Public.com, moomoo, and Robinhood (crypto) — plus a paper trading mode for risk-free testing. Trade across brokers from a single dashboard with automatic health monitoring and failover.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Social Trading -->
        <div class="landing-feature-detail" id="social">
            <div class="landing-feature-detail-icon"><i class="fa-duotone fa-rss fa-3x"></i></div>
            <div>
                <h2>Social Trading &amp; Subscriptions</h2>
                <p>Subscribe to strategies published by other traders and mirror their trades in your accounts. Publish your own strategies for others to follow. Subscription management handles notifications and updates when strategy parameters change. Build a community around your trading approach.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Backtesting & Analysis -->
        <div class="landing-feature-detail" id="backtesting">
            <div class="landing-feature-detail-icon"><i class="fa-duotone fa-flask-vial fa-3x"></i></div>
            <div>
                <h2>Backtesting &amp; Analysis</h2>
                <p>Test your strategies against historical market data before risking real capital. Run backtests over any date range and analyze performance metrics including Sharpe ratio, max drawdown, win rate, and profit factor. Use walk-forward analysis to validate that your strategy generalizes beyond the data it was tested on. Compare multiple backtests side by side, model slippage and commission costs, and optimize your strategies through data-driven iteration.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
